OL,3,CMurder with no motive: Inside the
OL,4,Ctrial of a dad who stabbed his only
OL,5,Cchild
OL,7,FForensic pathologist Dr Jennifer
OL,8,FBolton, who has decades of experience
OL,9,Fin criminal investigations, told the
OL,10,Fjury that the chance of Scarlett bring
OL,11,Fstabbed accidentally was "practically
OL,12,Fimpossible".
OL,14,FDr Bolton's findings were two-fold.
OL,15,FFirstly, that the 11cm wound that
OL,16,Fpierced Scarlett's lung and heart was
OL,17,Ffar too deep to have been cause by a
OL,18,Fknife laying on a kitchen counter.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
