OL,3,CMurder with no motive: Inside the
OL,4,Ctrial of a dad who stabbed his only
OL,5,Cchild
OL,7,FIt would never have had the continuous
OL,8,Fpressure needed to penetrate so far
OL,9,Finto a human body.
OL,11,FSecondly, that Scarlett ` who stood at
OL,12,F5ft6 ` was too tall for a knife laying
OL,13,Fon a counter to have reached as high
OL,14,Fas the flesh just below her left
OL,15,Fbreast where the blade had entered.
OL,17,FThese findings led to the
OL,18,Fpathologist's conclusion that only a
OL,19,Fknife held "firmly and deliberately in
OL,20,Fthe hand" could have led to this young
OL,21,Fgirl's fatal injury.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/9
